From b5a3247dc276b2fefe296d450f76ce0852b1ac29 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: =?UTF-8?q?Rom=C3=A1rio?= <rguisantos@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Sat, 13 Jun 2026 04:45:47 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] fix(mobile): peer deps do expo-router faltando (tela branca)
 + eas update
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

CAUSA PROVÁVEL da tela branca persistente: expo-router v4 depende de
react-native-reanimated e react-native-gesture-handler como peers, e
ambos estavam AUSENTES. Em dev o Metro tolera; no bundle release a
falta trava o boot do router → tela branca sem erro visível.

- react-native-reanimated ~3.16.1 e react-native-gesture-handler
  ~2.20.2 (versões do SDK 52)
- babel.config: plugin react-native-reanimated/plugin (obrigatório,
  por último)
- _layout: GestureHandlerRootView envolvendo a árvore (requisito do
  gesture-handler para funcionar em release)

Infra de OTA (eas update) para iterar sem rebuild nativo:
- expo-updates ~0.27.4
- runtimeVersion policy 'appVersion' + updates.fallbackToCacheTimeout 0
- eas.json com canais development/preview/production e
  EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL por perfil (ajustar a URL da Railway)
---
 apps/mobile/app.json        |  8 +++++++-
 apps/mobile/app/_layout.tsx |  9 ++++++---
 apps/mobile/babel.config.js |  6 +++++-
 apps/mobile/eas.json        | 22 ++++++++++++++++++++++
 apps/mobile/package.json    | 23 +++++++++++++----------
 5 files changed, 53 insertions(+), 15 deletions(-)
 create mode 100644 apps/mobile/eas.json

